76561198009582139,Recommended,287980,12243154,"Posted: 26 September, 2014",all,DannyBoy94,"This game is AMAZING! The graphics look excellent, it is challenging, fun, addictive and more. You get a map of a city with a few stations you work out where you want the lines to go, you get three lines to begin with and three locomotives. If you make it through to the next week (Sunday) you get to choose if you want to get a new line, tunnel or carriage as well as a locomotive which can be used on any current line or saved for a new line that you choose to build.This game is very impressive and it is still being developed, I am excited to see what the final result is as I already think this game fully deserves a 10/10 rating. It is well worth the £4.99 I spent on the game."
76561198127218584,Recommended,287980,29272224,Posted: 15 January,all,dholland,"A truly wonderful game. Can be enjoyed casually (just link up your network at random) but there really are more effective strategies. Each city has a unique feel because the random features (station positions and type) may be tweaked to give different proportions of station types and proportions of stations of different types on different land masses. Also, some cities have unique features like the Osaka shinkansen (fast trains) or slightly different weekly choices.There are basic achievements for each city, which lets you work out the basic mechanics of the game. Then there are more demanding achievements, with extra restrictions like only having tunnels on one line, and a much more demanding passenger target. These require a more efficient network since your network will start to crack under the strain well before you reach the passenger target. If the earlier incarnations of your network (when you have most opportunity for radical changes since there are not so many passengers) weren't efficient enough, then you likely won't make it (although you might if you're very lucky!)."
