76561198256388921,Recommended,287980,20932440,"Posted: 3 February, 2016",all,飛雪,"This is a nice and simple puzzle game that makes you connect 'stations' of various shapes with other 'stations' in order to use 'trams' to transport shapes to their corresponding station. The reason I put stations and trams in citation marks is because I think the theme of the game could easily be something else entirely. However does it matter that the theme is not the strongest? Not at all. Mini Metro is not a game that requires a lot of theme. It is a fun little puzzle game that gets harder as you progress and as you create more and more elaborate lines. I really enjoy how easy the game is to understand without the need of a text heavy tutorial. I like that the game maintains simplicity in design while adding complexity in the options the player will have to solve each puzzle. You can arrange and rearrange your lines as much as you like and you can deploy and redeploy trams and carriages at your convenience. So wherein lies the challenge? Well, to me, the challenge comes from a limited set of lines and trams available combined with a growing number of stations and passengers. A line that I might have had no problems with before, suddenly becomes overcrowded and I have to rearrange my lines or trams in order to deal with the situation before it is too late.Obviously, as the game is so simple and minimalistic, it is not something that I have played, or even see myself playing for hours on end. But I rather enjoy bringing it out when I have to kill a quarter of an hour or something along those lines. The puzzles change every time so I don’t feel like I’ve exhausted any of the cities in the game yet and in fact, some of the cities have now become a race against my own previous achievements. The game also has a nice tranquil feeling to the design to the point where it can feel both stressful to decide where to place the next line or which tram to give an extra carriage, as well as calming to watch the gentle movement on the pure white background.All in all, a good game worth a look if you’re into puzzle games."
