76561198083746631,Recommended,287980,19562087,"Posted: 8 December, 2015",all,Asalieri,"This is a truly unique game that should be in every puzzle lover's collection.It seems simple enough, make sure your passengers get to the stations they want to get to (your passengers being a wide array of shapes, denoting which station they want to travel to) and keep your subway system running as smoothly as possible until too many passengers overcrowd one station.It's the next Tetris. A deceptively simple brain teaser that progressively gets tougher and more unwieldy. I friggin LOVE it!You can spend hours just veging to this, and the sounds and music are relaxing and go very nicely with the game, it's an experience you should treat yourself to."
,Recommended,287980,18939502,"Posted: 7 November, 2015",all,[MoeGamer.net] Pete,"This is a wonderful, relaxing little puzzle game with an attractive, minimalist style to both its audio and visuals, and mechanics straightforward enough that the game never needs to explicitly spell them out for you. Despite the simplicity of the mechanics, though, this is a brainbender extraordinaire; those of you who enjoy setting up systems to work in the most efficient manner possible will have an absolute blast here.The concept is simple: you're in control of the subway system. Stations open across the map gradually, and you need to connect them with different coloured lines. Stations have different shapes, and the shapes of the ""commuters"" that appear at each station represent where they want to go. You will, then, need to plan out your routes so that there's minimal inefficiency; ""circle"" commuters will only ever want to go to ""square"" or ""triangle"" initially, for example, so there's little sense in making a line entirely out of circle stations.As the game progresses, the map expands and the number of possible shapes for the stations increases, too, until eventually you're having to consider things like interchanges extremely carefully as well as just the routes for your lines, particularly if you're playing on the ""Extreme"" mode, where once you've laid a line down, you can't change it!This is a highly enjoyable, inventive puzzle game, then, and particularly recommended to those who want something a little ""gentler"" than the big-budget fare of today!"
