76561198056424700,Not Recommended,287980,20613368,"Posted: 18 January, 2016",all,4ndr34,"Minimalism: It is a minimalist game, above all it is minimalist by design. You can readthis postby the developers of this game blog.The game is really, really minimalistic, do not misunderstand me, I like also minimalistic games, but the first Steam tag is ""Strategy"", then ""Simulation"" tag. Here you will find no strategy and no simulation, just minimalism.About the gameplay, you have very few things to control,stationspop out in the game randomly, and above all even if disconnected from trails thepeoplestart to wait and going upset if they are unable to reach their kind of destination. You have no money budget to spend in something you think you need when you need it, there is no construction costs, but instead, every week you could get a new train or a new trail or a new vagon or an interchange improvement for a station, or finally a new tunnel/bridge. Naturally you can only get your weekthingsbudget if and only if your week score is high enough...There is no construction or demolition time.Stationshave no range, just people that need to reach their kind of destination.If you change stations with nodes and people with weight you could play with a subset of the math graph theory...LOL...At the moment there is no editor.So, finally if and only if, you are looking for a really minimalistic game, you could be satisfied, apart the price that is not such a minimalistic price, maybe best to wait for sales, otherwise this game is really too much minimalistic...Sorry but, I have tonotsuggest this game to the public."
