76561198047772277,Recommended,287980,20032742,"Posted: 28 December, 2015",all,Skyra,"A puzzle game about building a highly abstracted mass transit system - there is no “solution” to the puzzles, just the question of how long you can keep meeting an ever rising demand.I admire both the aesthetic and pacing of this game.The interface is beautifully minimal, both providing everything you need to understand and play the game while evoking the classic topological underground map.The pacing is well executed with periods of calm where you feel in control, followed by periods of frantic activity as new stations and special stations force rapid change across your network.So why haven’t I played it more?Access to the depth - I don’t think the game lacks meaningful choices; when I look at the scores people have achieved (more than doubling my best on my most played cities) there are clearly things I can do to improve.  However the game progression doesn’t challenge me to discover new strategies or provide the signposts to improvement in the same way that my favourite puzzle games do.Well worth a look but don't be too shocked if the initial rush expires after 8-10 hours"
