,Not Recommended,287980,15068022,"Posted: 26 March, 2015",all,ioScream,"I love casual games, but I have to say this game is really boring. I know I haven't put much time in it, but that is because I got bored really quickly.This game feels like a more boring version of ""Pipe Dreams"", which for the younger crowd is a game where you have to build a piping system before liquid would flow and points were rewarded for the length of pipe the water traveled through before flooding out of the pipes.I digress. This game is about setting up a ""metro"" system to pick up shapes and deliver them to a station of the same shape. While you are setting up your ""tracks"" new shapes randomly appear as well as patrons. Those shapes have to be integrated into your system before the patrons get frustrated and leave at which point you lose.The bigger problem I have with this game is that there is no way of planning your system as the shape locations appear at random. There is a way to restructure your system but the interface feels unintuitive and I'm never sure if when I remove tracks/trams that they return to my inventory. From what I can tell - trams do not - and therefore you are punished for a restructure that you couldn't have planned before.This game feels like a mobile game, best experienced on the crapper.I hesitate to say this game is horrible as it has many great reviews, but as a fan of casual games - you can skip this one. Sorry devs.I will give this game more time and if my opinion changes I will update this review."
