76561198031266598,Recommended,287980,11689043,"Posted: 13 August, 2014",all,Rivano Moretti,"A classic game in the making. Having played only an hour and a half at the moment I can see myself loosing much more time to this game.While the lack of music is sad, being Early Access, I can't wait for the soundtrack to be added on.All in all, this is no train sim, it is a frustratingly fun strategists dream which challenges your abilities each time you play through and there is no forgiveness for even the slightest oversight. That being said, I would have liked a little tutorial that would have explained that when a new station appears on an existing line it becomes a place where trains blissfully roll by. Therefore, you must either redraw the entire line to include the new station or add it to another line.Graphically, the simplistic design is really quite beautiful and as time goes on you start to admire the mess of lines that begin to splay out as you try to balance length of lines and coverage.All in all, a great game and I highly recommend picking this game up while it is at a very reasonable price.On a lighter note, I now take my hat off to every Transport Minister past and present."
