,Recommended,287980,20061531,"Posted: 29 December, 2015",all,dinnersQuadron,"Do you like drawing lines, soft ambient sound effects, and urban planning?Then Mini Metro is just the game you need when you need a break from games involving actual serious urban planning. It's definitely a puzzle game, not a transport sim, but the sight of the little abstract metro trains gliding back and forth on the pleasantly coloured lines is still incredibly satisfying.The game challenges you to get all the geometric passengers to their matching destinations, and rewards you with additional tools at the end of every ""week"" in-game. Mini Metro is a fantastic, casual way to pass the time, but also includes several achievements that provide fascinating challenges within the scope of the game's easy-to-remember system of rules."
