,Recommended,287980,16871306,"Posted: 3 July, 2015",all,mmoran0032,"I started playing this game back when the beta number was in the single digits, and I have been very happy with how the development has progressed. The more recent changes (individualized cities being a huge change for the better) have been great without changing the game from its core.You lead the development of a single city's subway infrastructure to transport its citizens (circles, squares, triangles, and the like) to their desired station. Play starts off slowly, with passengers spawning quite slowly and you having a ton of resources at your disposal. Play difficulty (on the standard settings) quickly ramps up through the weeks to the point where you are just hanging on to your non-crowded stations...or you just lose because four stations go over the edge.You can also take the relaxing, almost theraputic route where you go for system efficiency. In this case, your upgrades come after reaching efficiency milestones instead of each week, but the goal is more relaxing to obtain.I'm looking forard to the soon-to-be-included soundtrack, which will finally make this a complete game (as much as I did like listening to movie soundtracks while playing)."
