,Recommended,287980,13057897,"Posted: 23 November, 2014",all,SanStarko,"This is a great little game, a simple to learn strategy/puzzle game that has that whole ""one more go"" aspect.All you need to do is link your different stations together and make sure the stations don't get too busy.  Yes you'll earn extra trains, extra carriages and extra lines.  But the whole game still comes down to the simple goal of linking your stations together.   You start with three stations and it seems an overly easy task but as the station start to increase so too does the difficulty and you find your metro system falling apart as you try to figure out the best way to connect them all.Thankfully there's the option to hit Pause, then delete all your lines and have a wee think about a new tactic, before finding that it works even worse than your previous layout.  Lots of different maps to play on too to give a bit of variety.As it's Early Access there are some things missing, no sound for example.  But the game idea is there and works perfectly and it can already keep you coming back over and over in it's current state.  It's well worth buying, especially considering how cheap it is."
