76561198062280225,Recommended,287980,14359244,"Posted: 6 February, 2015",all,Schmooze,"This is a fun and straightforward ""connect the dots"" game that becomes challenging and very addictive. The premise is a simple subway map from various cities and you connect different types of stations together using multiple connection points. Connect ▲ to █ to O and so on. As more stations become available they will show you passengers waiting and where they want to go. Before you know it you will have a bunch of people stuck waiting at station ▲ that all want to █ but to do so they need to connect through a third location.New stations will open up as the game moves. You begin with 3 stations and as time ticks past more and more open. It ramps up quickly and is moves along at a good pace. There are about 6 different cities to choose from which adds an addition level of difficulty. At the end of each week you are provided with an award which could be additional subway cars, new lines, or more tunnels. Playing in some of the more river heavy maps will require the use of lots of tunnels. As the weeks pass, your are map continue to grow allowing you more stations and of course more possibilities for heavy congestion.The game ends when your passengers give up on you and will no longer wait for a pickup. The city maps remain the same, but the actual station locations are a random spawn point making reply great.This is an in development app so there are some bugs to be expected. As of this review (02/06/2015) the only real game issue I think this had is the lack of sound. I am excited to see the new improvements and will keep plugging along with my subway maps."
,Recommended,287980,14377079,"Posted: 7 February, 2015",all,Lime,"Mini metro is a wonderful little time waster. if you've got a few minutes to kill and you want something simple to tide you over every now and then you could do far worse.There's something addictive about trying to build the perfect metro that can cope with whatever the game throws at you but you can only do that for so long before one backwater station gets overcrowded to the point of what I assume is acidental death when one of the little shapes falls onto the tracks because the station is packed full of other shapes waiting for their connection.It's simple fun really - there's not much more to it than that. I will say that once you figure out the formula to getting a decent high score the game starts to lose a lot of it's replay value but that said - I still pick it up now and then to kill time before I have to go to work in the morning.as a side note, It's lovely to see colourblind options for this game. along with that the UI is clean and eye pleasing."
