76561198192448238,Recommended,287980,28078919,"Posted: 29 November, 2016",all,ne555,"This game about building urban subway transit systems is deceptively deep. It looks at first glance like any typical, simplistic indie puzzle game, but very quickly you'll start to realize how sophisticated the game mechanics and AI actually are. The user interface, from the main menu, to the online high-score tables, to clicking-and-dragging your train tracks around the screen, are both super easy to use and very cool looking--and everything works flawlessly. The rules of the game are actually pretty complicated, and I won't go into them here--but you can start playing without much understanding of what's going on, and pick things up gradually and casually, which is a feature I always like... If you're interested in games that are super clean and cute, and easy to get started with, but then suck you into hours and hours of increasingly complex sessions, then here's one you definitely want to nab."
