76561197993657118,Recommended,287980,24573684,"Posted: 28 July, 2016",all,Paleorange,"I want to completely love Mini Metro, there is so much going for it, especially the perfectly executed interface and presentation, but before I can get to the point playing this game a lot more I get another circle shaped station that is obviously a system designed to eventually bring your train network to a halt (just google ""Mini Metro circle"" to get the idea of how much it annoys people). I think i'd rather have a totally RNG system for station shapes than the weighted system the game has now. It is so frustrating to find you have little choice but to link up 6 circle stations in a row and then watch the passengers pile up as full trains pass through with nowhere to offload their current passengers.If the previous paragraph made little sense to you then I suggest playing the demo which will demonstrate exactly what I mean. If you can put up with the constant frustration then underneath the surface is a fun little game that can allow you to while away the odd 30 minutes or so when you have the chance. I can't play more than 1-2 games at a time because of the issues, but I know i'll come back to it occasionally when the urge takes me, which is why I can just about recommend this game overall."
