76561198119250184,Recommended,287980,24342293,"Posted: 15 July, 2016",all,bigdaddy00,"This game is SO DAMN ADDICTING! I first found MM when NerdCubed reviewed it. I decided to give it a shot and honestly blew my mind. The game follows Harry Beck's map style from London Underground, and overall I love it. It is neat and organised. However, I have some recommendations for fixing bugs/tweaking the system.-I found a bug where you can connect more than 3 lines at once.Step 1: Find a place where three lines run with a curve between two stations.Step 2: Place a fourth line down, but on the opposite side.Step 3: Connect a fifth line to the left or right of the fourth line.Step 4: Repeat Step 3 if needed.- When you get far into the game, you sometimes would need a fourth line to travel in an area with three lines already (pain in the♥♥♥♥♥. What I think would be cool is a tunnel upgrade where you can have more than 3 lines per tunnel / track.-The spline points for some stations causes some of my lines to bend downward, when a prexisting station is 90 degrees to the left/right. Harry Beck would not do that. Especially in tunnels. It wastes more precious tunnels.-Speaking of tunnels, there should be a lot more tunnels you start with in London, Paris, NYC, Berlin, Cairo, Melbourne, and Auckland. It is so annoying.Like I said, overall, it is on my Top 10 best games ever played. And I have plaed a ton of games.  Looking forward to seeing this game grow in the near future."
76561198024272611,Recommended,287980,24306351,"Posted: 13 July, 2016",all,Ihatevans,"This is one of those games I was obsessed with for awhile.  It has a beautiful simplicity that makes me incredibly envious of as a game designer and entirely grateful for as a player.  Mini Metro is a balancing act that requires you to pay attention and plan ahead while you manage your resources in a totally unique way.  The game is so simple, but don't let that fool you - it's hard.  In a way this game reminds me of Diner Dash where it's a timed juggling act where you're constantly trying to keep your head above water, except there is no end (other than loss).   The game loop is incredibly addicting.My only complaint is I hate to start over each time.  It makes it a bit repetitive, but that's the nature of the game.This game is unique and totally worth checking out."
