,Recommended,287980,24240712,"Posted: 10 July, 2016",all,Loo,"This game is lovely.Build your own metro lines!Simply drag from one station to another to draw your line. The three basic stations are circle (common), triangle (uncommon) and square (rare), passengers will want to travel from their current station to a station that matches their shape, e.g. a triangle passenger currently at a circle station will want to go to a triangle station. Over time new unique station variants appear to complicate the map and other extras are introduced slowly.Pros:+ Intuative gameplay+ Very nice minimalistic art, simplistic interface and controls+ Relaxing background music and sound effects gel well with theme+ Idividual games are not too long, generally 30 minutes (+/- 10 minutes)+ Each map is different, with different rules and regulations, such as the maximum number of trains per line or number of seats per carriage - this is not explicitly stated in game (that I have seen) but these are nice to stumble across+ Very relaxing, a great game for stress reduction+ Features an even less stressful endless mode+ Very addictiveCons:- Removing stations from the middle of a line can be a bit fiddly but you will eventually get the hang of it (drag the line inbetween the station you want to remove and the next station over the station you want to remove)- The random station spawns can get frustrating when you have 5 circles in a row!Would very much recommend to anyone, especially for someone looking for a relaxing puzzle game or a building game5/5"
