,Recommended,287980,20730728,"Posted: 24 January, 2016",all,hedgemaze,"Mini Metro somehow manages to be very relaxing and also hectic and difficult at the same time. This is basically a perfect puzzle game, something you can easily play for a few minutes, but also a game with many different challenges and difficulty modes to always give you something new to try.You must plan the metro line for a simple, symbolic city as it grows, adding to the lines as more and more stations are added, while never having any station overcrowd. There is a zen about watching your tiny Vignelli city move and breathe, and odd pride in seeing your circles, squares and triangles successfully get to their destinations, but this gets harder and harder over time as your city grows. Each city is different in layout and many have special features, like bullet trains or trams which require different strategies, or different difficulties based on their unique logistics, like a city with many waterways to cross and few bridges with which to do it. I like that naturally you can decide which ways you like to play and spend time perfecting those, or you can experiment with different strategies. Loops, express lines, many short lines, several long lines, special lines? The game encourages you to try different things.There are also three different modes you can play in per city: Normal, which is as I described above; Endless, a zen sandbox experience where you can build your ideal system with stations never overcrowding; and Extreme, my favorite, the hard version of Normal, where every line and train you put down is permanent. Think carefully!The special achievements for each city are difficult and fun, things like ""Deliver 1500 passengers in Auckland using no more than two tunnels"" or ""Deliver 1200 passengers in São Paulo using only loops"", and will keep you occupied trying different strategies to make them happen. There's a daily challenge too with a different city and mode every day, so you can try your hand on the leaderboards.I've been playing Mini Metro since Early Access, before there were different real cities to play in, music, achievements, etc., and the game was already great as it was then. It's only astounded me how much more the developers were able to improve on it beyond that. The entire game is made with obvious quality and care.I can't recommend Mini Metro enough for anyone who likes puzzle games."
