,Recommended,287980,20951803,"Posted: 4 February, 2016",all,Big Willy,"Very simple and pretty game. The artstyle mimics that used by metropolitan rail maps around the world. Game play quickly becomes chaotic as you try to halt station overcrowding.It has good range of maps, from Paris to Melbourne and more, all with varying colour schemes, stations generated differently and slightly different assets available (Osaka and its high speed trains alongside regular locomotives and Cario with lower capacity trains being the most different).Additionally the Endless game mode creates a slower, less frantic experience, in which the end goal is to build an effient metro, not to prevent overcrowding at all costs, as is the goal in Normal mode.Extreme mode adds a different spin to Normal mode, not allowing you to rearrange your network once a station is connected, forcing you to think carefully about which line a station is best suited to.Although each game is short, it's incredibly easy to sink a lot of time into what is such a basic game, trying to create metro to get a new high score.Futhermore the acheivements provide fun challenges in the form of new ways to play on each cities.Well worth getting."
